J. D. HOWTH, Appellant, v. T. J. FARRAR et al., Appellee. No. 8545. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 25, 1938. For former opinion, see 94 F.2d 654,

Before HUTCHESON and HOLMES, Circuit Judges, and STRUM, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

As neither of the judges who concurred in the judgment of the court in the above numbered and entitled cause is of the opinion that the petition for rehearing should be granted, it is ordered that the said petition be, and the same hereby is, denied.
